    <h1>StartSchool Student Agreement for part-time studies</h1>

    <p>This agreement is concluded between</p>
    <p>
      (Name, Lastname)
      <strong>{{signer.name}} {{signer.surname}}</strong>, hereinafter Student,
      address at
      <strong>{{recipient_address}}</strong>, personal identity number
      <strong>{{signer.personal_code}}</strong>/ born on
      <strong>{{birthdate}}</strong>, and
    </p>
    <p>
      Tech Education Foundation, hereinafter StartSchool, address at Stabu iela
      50-9, LV-1011 Rīga, Latvia, registration No. 50008325331, represented by
      its member of the board Anna Andersone.
    </p>

    <p>The parties acknowledge the following:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        The purpose of StartSchool is to develop IT and entrepreneurial skills
        of the upcoming technology business leaders who are motivated to use
        these skills for advancement of their careers and of the businesses they
        work for, or businesses of their own, with a broader aim to increase the
        wellbeing of Latvian society.
      </li>
      <li>
        The Student has been selected as highly motivated and suitable candidate
        to join the StartSchool Program and as a person potentially capable of
        implementing the purpose of the StartSchool Program;
      </li>
      <li>
        Selection of the Student over hundreds of other candidates for
        participation in the StartSchool Program is considered as the trust of
        StartSchool in Student’s ability to most efficiently use the resources
        that are allocated to achieve the purpose of the StartSchool Program and
        not as an award or recognition for the Student’s previous achievements.
      </li>
      <li>
        Even if the Student is paying partial or full Tuition Fee, the Student
        benefits from the environment of studies and exchange of ideas and
        opinions created by involving other students who participate in the
        StartSchool Program thanks to the support of the donors;
      </li>
      <li>
        The donors and organizers of the StartSchool Program do not intend to
        impose any legal obligation regarding Student’s career choices after
        completion of the StartSchool Program, but expect Student to use the
        obtained skills and knowledge for advancement of the Student’s career or
        business and the Student’s commitment to to increase wellbeing of
        Latvian society. Considering the above acknowledgements, the parties
        agree as follows.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>1. Subject of the Agreement</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        This agreement provides for the terms under which the Student takes part
        in the education and mentoring program organized by StartSchool
        (hereinafter the StartSchool Program) and for the financial obligations
        of the Parties.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>2. General terms</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        The Study Period of the StartSchool Program starts on August 24, 2026.
        The Study Period ends at the moment of termination of the agreement.
      </li>
      <li>
        The Student shall be admitted to the StartSchool Program subject to
        timely payment of the monthly Tuition Fee as outlined in Clause 3 of
        this Agreement.
      </li>
      <li>
        StartSchool shall determine the structure and content of the Program.
        While the curriculum is generally uniform across all participants, the
        specific assignments, challenges, and expectations may vary based on the
        Student’s prior experience and demonstrated progress.
      </li>
      <li>
        The StartSchool Program is set up as a guided and mentored self-study
        program. The Student shall invest their effort in finding and studying
        the information independently, and shall not rely solely on the
        information or materials supplied by StartSchool.
      </li>
      <li>
        The following shall be available to the Student during the Study Period:
        <ul>
          <li>access to StartSchool education platform and StartSchool
            environment;</li>
          <li>live coding sessions with professionals;</li>
          <li>site visits to tech companies;</li>
          <li>access to a workplace at StartSchool office at StartupHouse,
            Lastādijas iela 12 k-3, Riga, subject to pre-booking and
            availability of the workplace.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Additional Resources for Tech + Startup Module Students
        <ul>
          <li>
            Students who are enrolled in the Tech + Startup Module (i.e., paying
            €400/month + VAT) will additionally receive access to:
            <ul>
              <li>Business workshops and lectures focused on startup
                development.</li>
              <li>Structured startup ideation and validation sessions;</li>
              <li>Fundraising preparation, pitching practice, and related
                training;</li>
              <li>Opportunities to engage in founder-specific mentoring.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Time Commitment
        <ul>
          <li>As a part-time student, the Student is expected to dedicate a
            minimum of 10 hours a week, with 2 hours dedicated to attending
            weekly coding sessions to make continuous progress through the
            assigned material and complete all required assignments and
            activities. While there is no fixed hourly requirement, StartSchool
            expects a consistent, sustained level of engagement, aligned with
            the selected module track. Students enrolled in the Tech + Startup
            Module should anticipate a higher time commitment compared to
            Tech-only participants.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        The student shall use such tools, systems, platforms and other resources
        for participation in the StartSchool Program and for completion of the
        specific assignments, as the StartSchool may assign. The Student shall
        comply with terms of use of these tools, systems, platforms and other
        resources as set by their providers.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>3. Tuition Type, Module Selection, and Payment Terms</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        Program Options and Tuition Fees
        <p>The Student is enrolled in the StartSchool Program as a part-time
          student and shall select one of the following module tracks:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Tech Module Only — Monthly Tuition Fee: €200 + VAT</li>
          <li>Tech + Startup Module — Monthly Tuition Fee: €400 +VAT</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Tuition Fee Payment Terms
        <ul>
          <li>The monthly tuition fee, as defined in clause 3.1, shall be paid
            in advance by the 25th calendar day of the previous month for the
            upcoming month.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        All payments shall be made by Stripe Payment Subscription link. By
        subscribing, you authorise Tech Education Foundation (StartSchool) to
        charge you according to the terms until you cancel.
        <ul>
          <li>Tech Module Subscription Payment link:
            <a
              href="https://buy.stripe.com/fZu00k5PZgIbepy4fY6wE00"
            >https://buy.stripe.com/fZu00k5PZgIbepy4fY6wE00</a></li>
          <li>Tech + Startup Module Subscription Payment link:
            <a
              href="https://buy.stripe.com/8x2dRa3HR77Bbdmh2K6wE01"
            >https://buy.stripe.com/8x2dRa3HR77Bbdmh2K6wE01</a></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Any payment is considered made when the money is received in the
        StartSchool’s bank account.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>4. Suspension and Rejoining the Program</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        The Student may request to temporarily suspend their participation in
        the StartSchool Program for a period of up to 12 months, due to
        personal, professional, or health-related reasons. The request must be
        submitted in writing to StartSchool and include a brief explanation 3
        working days before the billing date for the upcoming month to suspend
        participation starting with that month. The StartSchool shall notify the
        Student on granting the suspension via email.
      </li>
      <li>
        If the Student’s participation in the StartSchool Program has been
        suspended, then the performance of the obligations of the parties
        provided in this Agreement is suspended until the Student resumes the
        participation in the StartSchool Program, or this Agreement is
        terminated.
      </li>
      <li>
        The Student whose participation in the StartSchool Program has been
        suspended, may resume the participation in StartSchool in the following
        academic year. To resume the Student’s participation in the Program, the
        total period of suspension may not exceed 1 year.
      </li>
      <li>
        If the Student resumes the participation in the StartSchool Program, then
        the obligations of the Parties provided in this agreement resume. The
        Student shall not be required to repeatedly complete the part of the
        StartSchool Program they had completed until suspension.
      </li>
      <li>
        If the Student neither notifies StartSchool on resuming of the Student’s
        participation, nor requests the extension by the deadline and as
        otherwise provided in Clause 4 of this Agreement, then it is considered
        that the Student has withdrawn themself from the Agreement on the day
        when the term for notification or the resumption has expired.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>5. Ongoing Participation Beyond Study Period</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        Ongoing Participation
        <ul>
          <li>The Student’s participation in the StartSchool Program is not
            limited to a fixed duration.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Updated Modules and Fees
        <ul>
          <li>StartSchool may update the program structure, learning modules,
            and tuition fees over time. Any such changes will be communicated to
            the Student in writing at least 30 days in advance and shall apply
            from the following calendar month, unless otherwise agreed.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Termination by Student
        <ul>
          <li>The Student may withdraw from the Program at any time by submitting
            written notice to StartSchool no later than 5 working days prior to
            the billing day of the upcoming month. Withdrawal becomes effective
            on the last day of the month in which the notice is submitted, unless
            the Student requests a later effective date.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Termination by StartSchool
        <ul>
          <li>StartSchool may terminate the Student’s participation by providing
            at least 30 days’ notice, except in cases of breach of agreement,
            Code of Conduct or failure to meet performance obligations, in which
            case immediate termination may apply.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Effect of Termination
        <ul>
          <li>Upon termination, the Student is responsible for all tuition fees
            due up to and including the final month of participation. No refunds
            will be issued for months already commenced.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>6. Effective Date and Termination</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        Effective Date and Duration
        <ul>
          <li>This Agreement enters into force on the date of the last signature
            and shall remain effective on an ongoing, indefinite basis unless
            terminated by either party in accordance with this Clause.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Termination by the Student
        <ul>
          <li>The Student may terminate this Agreement at any time by notifying
            StartSchool in writing via email to start@startschool.org no later
            than 5 working days before the billing date for the upcoming calendar
            month.</li>
          <li>The Agreement shall be considered terminated on the last day of the
            month in which the notice is submitted, unless the Student requests a
            later termination date.</li>
          <li>Paid tuition fees are non-refundable, and the Student remains
            responsible for tuition fees for all calendar months commenced prior
            to the termination date.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Termination by StartSchool
        <ul>
          <li>
            StartSchool may terminate this Agreement:
            <ul>
              <li>At will, by giving the Student at least 30 days' written
                notice;</li>
              <li>
                With immediate effect, in case of any of the following:
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    The Student fails to meet the performance standards set by
                    the Program Manager, including but not limited to:
                    <ul>
                      <li>Failure to follow the required program pace;</li>
                      <li>Participation in less than 50% of required activities
                        without a valid reason;</li>
                      <li>Consistent failure to meet assignment or project
                        milestones;</li>
                    </ul>
                  </li>
                  <li>The Student materially breaches the Code of Conduct;</li>
                  <li>The Student’s continued participation is found to be
                    incompatible with the goals of StartSchool.</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Code of Conduct Violations
        <ul>
          <li>The Code of Conduct is annexed to and forms an integral part of
            this Agreement.</li>
          <li>
            In case of a Code of Conduct violation:
            <ul>
              <li>A first breach will result in a written warning and
                discussion;</li>
              <li>A second breach may result in referral to the Disciplinary
                Committee;</li>
              <li>A third breach or Disciplinary Committee recommendation may
                result in immediate termination of this Agreement by
                StartSchool.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Financial Obligations Upon Termination
        <ul>
          <li>
            If the Agreement is terminated for any reason, the Student is
            responsible for:
            <ul>
              <li>All tuition fees accrued up to and including the final month of
                participation;</li>
              <li>Any late payment penalties (0.1% per overdue day) if
                applicable;</li>
              <li>No refunds will be issued for months already commenced.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Refund in Case of Early Termination by StartSchool
        <ul>
          <li>If StartSchool terminates the Agreement at will (i.e. not due to
            Student breach), and the Student has pre-paid tuition for future
            months, StartSchool will refund the portion of the tuition
            corresponding to the period after the effective termination
            date.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>7. Information and confidentiality</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        The Student shall not disclose to third parties the information about the
        process of implementation of the StartSchool Program, that, if learned
        by third parties, may cause violation of other person's rights or damage
        to the reputation of StartSchool or to the StartSchool Program. The
        Student may reveal the information about its participation in the
        StartSchool Program insofar as it pertains only to the Student and does
        not include information about other persons without their express
        consent.
      </li>
      <li>
        The Student agrees that their participation in the StartSchool Program
        activities and assignments may be recorded in photographs or on video
        and such recordings may be used to illustrate the StartSchool Program and
        the StartSchool Program for a non-commercial purpose.
      </li>
      <li>
        The Student hereby irrevocably permits StartSchool to use for educational
        purposes and for promotion of StartSchool and the StartSchool Program any
        material that the Student has prepared or made available to StartSchool or
        the involved tutors, mentors or other StartSchool personnel, in course of
        the Student's participation in the StartSchool Program. The permission
        especially enables StartSchool to use such material for tuition of other
        StartSchool Program students. The permission is effective worldwide and
        without limitation of the term. The Student hereby acknowledges that by
        receiving the education provided by StartSchool the value whereof exceeds
        the Student's payments to StartSchool, the Student has received sufficient
        compensation for the permission stated in this clause and hereby waives
        all claims for the remuneration in relation to the permission granted
        under this clause and in relation to use of the material in compliance
        with this permission. The permission does not apply to the parts of such
        material that are expressly noted as developed or authored by persons
        other than the Student (e.g., quotes, reused software code, etc.).
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>8. Final provisions</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        The relationship arising from this agreement is governed by the normative
        acts effective in the Republic of Latvia.
      </li>
      <li>
        Amendments to this agreement are effective if formalized in writing and
        signed by the parties.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>9. Particulars of the parties</h2>
    <ol>
